      "fontSize": 14, "fontFamily": 2,
      "text": "Requirements (R)",
      "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null, "originalText": "Requirements (R)",
      "autoResize": true, "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "el06", "type": "text",
      "x": 18, "y": 122, "width": 442, "height": 600, "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#343a40", "backgroundColor": "transparent", "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1, "strokeStyle": "solid", "roughness": 0, "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [], "frameId": null, "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [], "updated": 1, "link": null, "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 12, "fontFamily": 2,
      "text": "R0  ● Core goal\n    At every garment selection surface (catalog browser,\n    quote picker), favorited items surface first\n\nR1  ● Must-have\n    Three-tier preferences: brand / styles / color groups\n    — all brand-anchored, no global scope\n  R1.1 ● Must  Brand favorites (ordering; non-favorited accessible)\n  R1.2 ● Must  Style favorites per brand\n  R1.3 ● Must  Color group favorites (colorGroupName level)\n\nR2  ● Undecided  →  [RESOLVED: V2 — no customers table yet]\n    Customer prefs override shop defaults when active\n    Priority: customer › shop › everything else\n\nR3  ● Must-have\n    Cross-brand read-only overview of all saved favorites\n\nR4  ● Must-have\n    Color/style editing requires explicit single-brand context\n\nR5  ● Must-have\n    Unfavoriting never erases data (soft-delete)\n    Re-enabling restores prior selections\n\nR6  ● Must-have\n    Prefs stored at (brand_id, colorGroupName)\n    NOT at individual catalog_colors row level\n\nR7  ● Undecided  →  [LEAN YES — same tables as R1]\n    Data model queryable by quote picker\n    given (scope, brand_id) → ordered favorites list\n\nR8  ● Must-have\n    Clear nav home + stable, bookmarkable URL",
      "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null, "originalText": "R0 requirements...",
      "autoResize": true, "lineHeight": 1.4
    },

