      "groupIds": [], "frameId": null, "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [], "updated": 1, "link": null, "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 11, "fontFamily": 3,
      "text": "Req    Status        Description                        A    B    C\n─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nR0     Core goal     Favorited items surface first      ✅   ✅   ✅\nR1     Must-have     Three-tier preferences per brand   ✅   ✅   ✅\nR1.1   Must-have     Brand favorites (ordering only)    ✅   ✅   ✅\nR1.2   Must-have     Style favorites per brand          ✅   ✅   ✅\nR1.3   Must-have     Color group favorites (name lvl)   ✅   ✅   ✅\nR2     V2 (blocked)  Customer prefs override shop       ✅   ✅   ✅\nR3     Must-have     Cross-brand read-only overview     ✅   ✅   ✅\nR4     Must-have     Single-brand editing context       ✅   ✅   ✅\nR5     Must-have     Soft-delete: data never lost       ✅   ✅   ✅\nR6     Must-have     Prefs at colorGroupName+brand_id   ✅   ✅   ✅\nR7     Lean yes      Queryable by quote picker          ✅   ✅   ✅\nR8     Must-have     Clear nav home + bookmarkable URL  ✅   ✅   ❌\n─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n       VERDICT                                         OK   OK  FAIL\n\nNotes:\n• A and B pass all requirements.\n• C fails R8 only: settings placement buries a\n  daily-use operational feature under Settings —\n  wrong mental model for quoting work.\n• DP1 (A vs B): both pass. Decision is about nav\n  prominence — sub-item under Garments vs own entry.\n  Shape B also cleans up by replacing Color Settings\n  (which this feature fully supersedes).",
      "textAlign": "left", "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null, "originalText": "Fit check table",
      "autoResize": true, "lineHeight": 1.5
    },

